{"data": [{"id": "4743491", "title": "Tesla: A Golden Buying Opportunity", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2165724846/image_2165724846.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"\u041a\u0438\u0431\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0440\u0443\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043a Tesla \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043f\u0430\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d \u0432 \u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0435, \u044d\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u0410\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0438\u043a\u0435\" data-id=\"2165724846\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2165724846/image_2165724846.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2165724846/image_2165724846.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2165724846/image_2165724846.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2165724846/image_2165724846.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2165724846/image_2165724846.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2165724846/image_2165724846.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2165724846/image_2165724846.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2165724846/image_2165724846.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">Veronique D/iStock Editorial via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>Introduction</h2> <p>I feel good because Tesla (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TSLA\" title=\"Tesla, Inc.\">TSLA</a></span>) has rallied by 77% since my bullish call <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4720182-tesla-stock-the-case-for-buying-now\">on September 10</a>. I think that the rally was fueled by robust fundamental factors and there is</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2165724846/image_2165724846.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743491-tesla-tsla-stock-a-golden-buying-opportunity", "pub_date": "2024-12-11 20:30:00"}, {"id": "4743641", "title": "Another 50bp Bank Of Canada Cut, But Smaller Moves Lie Ahead", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/846636558/image_846636558.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Close up of Canadian banknotes (CAD) background\" data-id=\"846636558\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/846636558/image_846636558.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/846636558/image_846636558.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/846636558/image_846636558.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/846636558/image_846636558.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/846636558/image_846636558.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/846636558/image_846636558.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/846636558/image_846636558.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/846636558/image_846636558.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">MJ_Prototype</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p><em>By <a href=\"https://think.ing.com/author/james-knightley/\" rel=\"nofollow\">James Knightley</a></em></p> <h2><span>Growing economic slack prompts a second consecutive 50bp rate cut</span></h2> <p>Bank of Canada has cut its policy interest rate 50bp to 3.25%, as expected. Last week's surprise jump in unemployment to 6.8% from 6.5% helped cement the call, but inflation</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/846636558/image_846636558.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743641-another-50bp-bank-of-canada-cut-smaller-moves-lie-ahead", "pub_date": "2024-12-11 20:25:00"}, {"id": "4743627", "title": "Immunome: A Recently Acquired Lead Asset And A Small Market", "description": "<figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1445810160/image_1445810160.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"House on the edge\" data-id=\"1445810160\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1047px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1445810160/image_1445810160.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1445810160/image_1445810160.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1445810160/image_1445810160.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1445810160/image_1445810160.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1445810160/image_1445810160.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1445810160/image_1445810160.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1445810160/image_1445810160.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1445810160/image_1445810160.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">PM Images</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>Immunome (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IMNM\" title=\"Immunome, Inc.\">IMNM</a></span>) is a late stage developer of cancer therapies. Its lead asset is AL102, a gamma secretase inhibitor in a Phase 3 trial for the treatment of desmoid tumor. All other assets are preclinical.</p> <h2>Background</h2> <p>Immunome has a turbulent</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1445810160/image_1445810160.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743627-immunome-a-recently-acquired-lead-asset-and-a-small-market", "pub_date": "2024-12-11 20:20:22"}, {"id": "4743624", "title": "NexGen Energy's Offtake Agreement: A De-Risking Event, A Confirmation Of The Uranium Bull Market", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1304747275/image_1304747275.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Uranium, a chemical element with a U symbol and an atomic mass equal to 238 u, has an atomic number 92\" data-id=\"1304747275\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1304747275/image_1304747275.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1304747275/image_1304747275.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1304747275/image_1304747275.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1304747275/image_1304747275.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1304747275/image_1304747275.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1304747275/image_1304747275.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1304747275/image_1304747275.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1304747275/image_1304747275.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">RHJ</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>What</h2> <p>On December 4, 2024, <em>NexGen Energy Ltd</em>. (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NXE\" title=\"NexGen Energy Ltd.\">NXE</a></span>) <a href=\"https://www.nexgenenergy.ca/news/news-details/2024/NexGen-Announces-First-Uranium-Sales-Contracts-for-5-Million-Pounds-with-Major-US-Utilities/default.aspx\" rel=\"nofollow\">announced</a> its first uranium sales agreements, signed with multiple U.S. utilities, to supply 1 Mlb per year of U3O8 from 2029 to 2033 from its flagship Rook I project in</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1304747275/image_1304747275.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743624-nexgen-energy-offtake-agreement-de-risking-event-confirms-uranium-bull-market", "pub_date": "2024-12-11 20:14:53"}, {"id": "4743623", "title": "Tesla's Path To $424 By Year-End", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1997223655/image_1997223655.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Electric Car Charging\" data-id=\"1997223655\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"864px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1997223655/image_1997223655.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1997223655/image_1997223655.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1997223655/image_1997223655.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1997223655/image_1997223655.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1997223655/image_1997223655.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1997223655/image_1997223655.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1997223655/image_1997223655.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1997223655/image_1997223655.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">3alexd</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>Investment Thesis</h2> <p>Since our <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4730066-why-teslas-growth-isnt-slowing\">last coverage</a>, <b>Tesla, Inc.</b> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TSLA\" title=\"Tesla, Inc.\">TSLA</a></span>) has appreciated approximately 44%, propelled by optimism over Donald Trump\u2019s re-election. Anticipation of business-friendly policies, probable rollbacks on EV tax credit caps, and strong links with the administration by CEO</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1997223655/image_1997223655.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743623-teslas-path-to-424-by-year-end", "pub_date": "2024-12-11 20:04:55"}, {"id": "4743622", "title": "Cineverse: An Incredible Micro-Cap Setup", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/186817529/image_186817529.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"light bulb with dollar sign drawn on a blackboard\" data-id=\"186817529\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1020px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/186817529/image_186817529.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/186817529/image_186817529.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/186817529/image_186817529.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/186817529/image_186817529.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/186817529/image_186817529.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/186817529/image_186817529.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/186817529/image_186817529.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/186817529/image_186817529.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">Hiob/E+ via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div></p> <p><span>Listen here or on the go via </span><a href=\"https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/stock-market-live/id1653747327\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noopener\">Apple Podcasts</a><span> and </span><a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/show/30dUmqhaQJlW7qWiyltTNB?si=4cdae8002b3f492f\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Spotify</a></p> <p><div class=\"pcast hidden-print\">\n  <div class=\"pcast__section-1\">\n    <img alt=\"\" class=\"pcast__top-img pcast__marketing\" src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2018/11/21/podcast_series_header.png\">\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"pcast__section-2\"><iframe src=\"https://widget.spreaker.com/player?episode_id=63268311&amp;theme=light&amp;playlist=false&amp;playlist-continuous=false&amp;chapters-image=true&amp;episode_image_position=right&amp;hide-logo=true&amp;hide-likes=true&amp;hide-comments=true&amp;hide-sharing=true&amp;hide-download=true&amp;color=ff6900\" width=\"100%\" height=\"200px\" frameborder=\"0\" sap-id=\"15\"></iframe></div>\n  <div class=\"pcast__section-3\">\n    <div class=\"pcast__ad-container\"></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n</p> <p>Courage &amp; Conviction Investing shares why he finds Cineverse (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CNVS\" title=\"Cineverse Corp.\">CNVS</a></span>) to be one of the most incredible micro-cap setups right now. <em>This is an excerpt from a </em><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4739406-the-art-of-being-a-contrarian-with-courage-and-conviction-investing\"><em>recent conversation.</em></a></p> <p><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/checkout/mp_1132#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link\"><strong>Subscribe to Courage &amp; Conviction Investing's Second Wind Capital</strong></a></p> <p>Transcript</p> <p><strong>Courage &amp; Conviction Investing: </strong>I started <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4730825-cineverse-corp-owns-terrifier-3-and-few-people-have-connected-the-dots\">talking</a> about Cineverse (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CNVS\" title=\"Cineverse Corp.\">CNVS</a>) privately to my group on October 18th. When I broke it, the stock was 2.10 and I teed up the situation.</p> <p>We own about 4% of the business across all accounts, excluding my Seeking Alpha members, so I have no idea how many shares they own. And this is one of the most incredible setups in micro caps.</p> <p>What basically happened is they own the rights to Terrifier 3, which did $54 million at the box office domestically. The way the math works, just kind of synthesizing what you can find on Google and reading Reddit posts and whatnot, is when you sell a movie at the box office, you get 45% unless you're a big Hollywood studio of the money of the box, of the gate, so to speak.</p> <p>And the way the math, I believe, worked here was they had a loan for like $3.7 million with interest. And then they had marketing expenses to market this. The first $12.5 million at the box office, they get 45%. They get, I believe, get 100% of that, they can pay back their debtholders, and they can get reimbursed on the expenses. And then from $12.5 million to $54 million, you multiply that by about 20% or 19%.</p> <p>So for a company, and we were buying at like a $33 million market cap, they had like maybe $5 million of debt. Now granted back on October 15th, they hadn't done $54 million in at the box office. But that to me, it looked like a pretty good bet, given how strong they came out of the gate.</p> <p>And so this is a company that's going to get a $14 million cash windfall, okay, with a $33 million market cap. And then when I read the <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CNVS/earnings/transcripts#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link\">conference calls</a> and I synthesized it, I said, \u201cAll right, they took $9 million SG&amp;A out of cost the past year. They own Match Point, which is an incredible technology.</p> <p>So they have the ability because they own $40 million library of film, of content. Because they run 30 different fast channels, including Bob Ross channel, Dog Whisperer and whatnot. So they spent tens of millions of dollars to build this technology. It's unmatched, it's unrivaled.</p> <p>And so with AI, when these AI engines want to ingest this data, the video, it doesn't work for Hollywood studios and that was a great explanation of that on the <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4737672-cineverse-corp-cnvs-q3-2024-earnings-call-transcript\">conference call</a>.</p> <p>Corsair is a $0.5 billion fund. They took a 5% stake. Jay was on the conference call and they explained it. So the other thing is if you think about the ecosystem, they own all these FAST channels, so there's 80 million views I believe, and they have cineSearch, which they're working on Google (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GOOGL\" title=\"Alphabet Inc.\">GOOGL</a>) (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GOOG\" title=\"Alphabet Inc.\">GOOG</a>), which should be very valuable.</p> <p>They own Bloody and Disgusting, which is, I believe, one of the top 20 podcasts in America. They got a great podcast business, and they also own a streaming business called Screambox. So they should dominate the horror genre, and they can replicate this playbook what they did with Terrifier 3. They already signed another deal for next Christmas. So it's an incredibly exciting business.</p> <p>No one knows about it. I put it on the free site with a lag. No one's ever heard of the company, everyone's looking backwards and I'm like, \u201cThis is a layup, okay?\u201d</p> <p>The business is literally inflecting. This thing could be a $10 stock. How the hell will we be able to buy, what do we buy, 600,000 shares of this thing, between 175 and 230 or 240, whatever the heck we paid for it. And so it'll be very interesting to watch what happens.</p> <p>They had a good Q2, their fiscal year ends starts April 1st. So the Q3, which is December 31, 2024, they're going to blow the doors off of numbers. And the analysts, the two analysts that cover it, Benchmark and Alliance, they'll take their numbers up. That's, I think, why it's one of the stocks having a nice move today.</p> <p>But what's so lucrative about this stuff? When you get these things right that no one knows about, no one's thinking about, is there's only 15.7 million shares outstanding and management owns a ton of stock. Corsair owns 5.5% of the <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CNVS/virtual_analyst_report\">company</a>.</p> <p>So there's not a lot of float available. So that first-mover advantage is incredibly valuable. But if the stock moves up a point, that's 50% on your original basis, thereabouts, right? And it's only a $15.7 million change in market cap.</p> <p>Because of the tremendous free cash flow, they're going to pay off all their debt, they're going to license Terrifier 3, I believe, to Amazon (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMZN\" title=\"Amazon.com, Inc.\">AMZN</a>), because Terrifier 2 is on Amazon 2. And then they'll have ancillary revenue through that share. They have first right of refusal Terrifier 4, and they could put it on Screambox, which is $4.99 a month. And then they can sell DVDs to Walmart (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WMT\" title=\"Walmart Inc.\">WMT</a>). So bundle Terrifier 2 and Terrifier 3.</p> <p>Those are the gems. I try to find one or two of those a year. I've been better at finding. And this idea came from the guy I work with in Greenwich who's had a family office for 20 years. His fund got up to $180 million, and he's got a big Wall Street network. He said, \u201cHey, take a look at this thing. I think you may like it.\u201d And then I dropped everything. I spent like eight hours working on it that day and I said, \u201cOh my God, this is amazing.\u201d</p> <p>Those are fun. Those are special. And again, if you get two of these a year, and I've been good about finding two, three, four sometimes, that's how the serious, serious money gets made. The only issue is, the liquidity has stepped up a bunch now, but it's still a small company.</p> <p>So it's not anything any big players could size. But for retail investors, like, I'm sure I have members that bought 5,000 shares, or maybe 10,000 shares. It's a good one, right? You buy it at $2, $2.25, $2.40, and I think it was pushing $3.90 today, and I think it'd go a lot higher. But again, it's going to be very volatile, but that's the magic.</p> <p>That's what I'm trying to find. That's what I'm trying to get back to. And it's really just a function of bandwidth. Like how do you spend your time? Bandwidth is incredibly valuable.</p> <p>You never know when you're going to see a great idea. But if you're not in the trenches every day, learning, reading, synthesizing, getting better, learning from mistakes, you're going to miss these things. Because there's no bell that rings and says, \u201cOh, there's a great opportunity like you have to go and get them.</p> <p>You have to go find them. You have to be on a quest.\u201d It's an adventure. You're going to have setbacks, but you have to stick to that North Star. And that's what we're trying to do.</p><div class=\"before_last_paragraph-piano-placeholder\"></div><p>Editor's Note: This article covers one or more microcap stocks. Please be aware of the risks associated with these stocks.</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/186817529/image_186817529.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743622-cineverse-an-incredible-micro-cap-setup", "pub_date": "2024-12-11 20:00:00"}, {"id": "4743617", "title": "November CPI: General Disinflation Stalls But Services And Shelter Cool", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2165462299/image_2165462299.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Woman shopping at a convenience store and checking her receipt\" data-id=\"2165462299\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"102